clinicalHistory.guidelineTitle: Laboratory Evidence of Immunity or confirmation of Hepatitis A disease

groupContraindication.contraindicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has had an adverse reaction to a vaccine component.

groupContraindication.observationTitle: Severe allergic reaction after previous dose of Hepatitis A
groupContraindication.contraindicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has had a severe allergic reaction after a previous dose of Hepatitis A vaccine.
Do not vaccinate if the patient has had a severe allergic reaction to neomycin.
Do not vaccinate if the patient has a hypersensitivity to alum.

vaccineContraindication.contraindicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has a hypersensitivity to yeast.

observationCode.text: Close contact with international adoptee during first 60 days

indication.description: Administer to persons who will have close contact with an international adoptee during the first 60 days.
indication.guidance: The first dose of the 2-dose hepatitis A vaccine series should be administered as soon as adoption is planned, ideally 2 or more weeks before the arrival of the adoptee.
